🎬 Why NOT just use video?

You should use video when:

You just want a visual background

No interaction needed

Fast implementation matters

👉 That’s 80% of websites.

🧠 Why people use frame-based animation instead

Because it unlocks things video cannot do:

1. 🎮 Scroll-controlled animation

Animation moves based on scroll

Like Apple product pages

👉 Video can’t sync perfectly with scroll

2. 🧩 Interactivity

React to mouse movement

Pause/play at specific frames

Jump to states dynamically

👉 Video is linear (play → pause → done)

3. 🎯 Precise control

Stop at exact frame

Reverse animation

Slow down specific sections

👉 Video = limited control

4. 🧠 Logic-driven visuals

Example:

Idea grows when user clicks

Network expands based on input

👉 You can’t “program” a video like that

🔥 Where this technique is ACTUALLY used
✅ 1. Premium product sites

Apple AirPods / iPhone pages

Scroll → product rotates / evolves

✅ 2. Storytelling landing pages

Startup explaining concept visually

Step-by-step animation

✅ 3. Data / concept visualization

Networks (like your Trade an Idea 👀)

Systems evolving over time

✅ 4. Interactive portfolios

Designer/dev showing creativity

Not just static visuals

⚖️ Honest Pros & Cons
✅ Pros (Frame-based)

Full control over animation

Scroll + interaction support

Unique, high-end feel

Can integrate with logic

❌ Cons (Frame-based)

Heavy (many images)

Complex to build

Can lag on mobile

Harder to optimize

✅ Pros (Video)

Super easy

Lightweight (if compressed well)

Works everywhere

Fast to deploy

❌ Cons (Video)

No interactivity

No scroll sync

Limited control

Feels generic

🧠 Real takeaway

👉 Use video for:

Clean, simple, fast landing pages

👉 Use frame animation for:

Interactive, storytelling, premium experiences
